When a AJS.InlineDialog is displayed to the user and he clicks an an element in the dialog, then the dialog is closed. 
We are using InlineDialog in the Tempo Plugin to allow user to quickly edit issue worklogs and works great in JIRA 4.2. But like many other AUI features that we are using, this behaves differently in JIRA 4.3 and results in that the user can't click on the worklogs to change them since the dialog closes immediately. There is also no option in InlineDialog to disable automatically closing the dialog on click.

We are using AJS.InlineDialog as documented here: http://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=215486613
The issue can not be reproduced in the InlineDialog demo page: https://studio.atlassian.com/source/browse/~raw,r=61852/AJS/trunk/src/samples/inline-dialog/inline-dialog.html

The source seems to that the showPopup method in InlineDialog binds a "showLayer" with the type "inlineDialog". 
When a click event on the layer is triggered, the following code is executed:

{code}
            var topWindow = getWindow().AJS;
            if (topWindow.currentLayerItem &&  topWindow.currentLayerItem.type !== "popup") { // type is "inlineDialog"

                if (topWindow.currentLayerItem._validateClickToClose) {
                    if (topWindow.currentLayerItem._validateClickToClose(e)) {
                        topWindow.currentLayerItem.hide();
                    }
                } else {
                    topWindow.currentLayerItem.hide(); // this gets called
                }
            }
{code}

That is, since the type is not "popup", the hide method on the item is called.

